  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-07-21",
    "date": "2022-02-25T15:08:04Z",
    "text": "Securing Our Border States Act\n\nThis bill requires the Department of the Treasury to provide grants to states for building barriers and related infrastructure along the U.S.-Mexico border.\n\nWithin 30 days of receiving a certification from a border state that it intends to use such grant funding for constructing a border barrier, Treasury must disburse funds to the state, with the amount based on the number of miles of border in that state that currently does not have a border barrier.\n\nThe bill provides $22 billion of funding for this grant program and permanently rescinds $22 billion from funds made available for various assistance programs related to COVID-19."
  },
